{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17595983","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17595983"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:09:34+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:09:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15387"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15387","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15387"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.5,0.05,0.1,0.3,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8078"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63707"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8078","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8078"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15387"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49146"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"504"},{"type":"tags","id":"3696"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4978"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19604"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19606"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20887"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63707","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/63707"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EIrritable bowel syndrome (IBS) is a chronic functional gastrointestinal disorder characterised by abdominal pain and altered bowel habits in the absence of structural abnormalities. There are various strategies and interventions that can be considered in the management of this problem.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is most effective in improving symptomatic relief?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["High-fibre diet","Prolonged fasting","Probiotic supplements","Psychological therapy","Regular laxative use"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPsychological therapy,\u003C/strong\u003E including cognitive behavioural therapy and stress management is a cornerstone of IBS treatment, as psychological factors significantly influence symptom severity and frequency.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Ehigh-fibre diet\u003C/strong\u003E may actually worsen symptoms in some IBS patients, particularly those with predominant diarrhoea. A \u003Cstrong\u003Eregular laxative\u003C/strong\u003E regimen is not recommended as first-line therapy and may lead to dependency. \u003Cstrong\u003EProlonged fasting\u003C/strong\u003E can exacerbate symptoms and negatively impact nutritional status. While \u003Cstrong\u003Eprobiotic supplements\u003C/strong\u003E show some promise, evidence for their effectiveness remains inconsistent.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe most effective approach combines psychological support with dietary modifications (such as low FODMAP diet), regular exercise, and stress management techniques.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Irritable bowel syndrome (IBS) has a significant psychological component that affects symptom severity.","Management of IBS requires a biopsychosocial approach including dietary modification, stress management, and lifestyle changes.","Low FODMAP diet is an evidence-based dietary intervention for IBS symptom management."],"references":["Ford AC, Sperber AD, Corsetti M, Camilleri M. Irritable bowel syndrome. Lancet. 2020 Nov 21;396(10263):1675-1688. doi: 10.1016/S0140-6736(20)31548-8. Epub 2020 Oct 10. PMID: 33049223","Camilleri M. Diagnosis and Treatment of Irritable Bowel Syndrome: A Review. JAMA. 2021 Mar 2;325(9):865-877. doi: 10.1001/jama.2020.22532. Erratum in: JAMA. 2021 Apr 20;325(15):1568. doi: 10.1001/jama.2021.4833. PMID: 33651094","Patel N, Shackelford KB. Irritable Bowel Syndrome. [Updated 2022 Oct 30]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK534810/","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Scienc"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49146"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15387"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49146","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/49146"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-22T11:38:48+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-22T11:39:18+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8078"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63707"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udfad","name":"Psychiatry","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{